        <template id="section-brew">
          <h2>Brewing a Vietnamese coffee cup together</h2>
          <div class="content">
            <p class="small">Do not pick up any coffee or drinks or whatsoever from the cafeteria, we got something better!!!</p>
            <ol>
              <li>Heat water just off boil (≈ 96°C).</li>
              <li>Add 2–3 tbsp medium‑coarse Vietnamese coffee to the <em>phin</em>.</li>
              <li>Bloom with a splash of hot water (20–30s), then fill and let drip 4–5 minutes.</li>
              <li>Stir in 1–2 tbsp condensed milk.</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="small">Tip: Use a slightly coarser grind than espresso to avoid clogging the phin.</p>
          </div>
        </template>

